MPUMALANGA police have launched a manhunt for a gang of three gunmen, who robbed a Putco bus in Vlaklaagte No 2 in Tweefonein on Wednesday, 26 January. Brigadier Selvy Mohlala said a driver of a Putco bus was transporting commuters from Tweefontein K to Tweefontein A. “While at the bus stop at Tweefontein A waiting for passengers to get inside, three unknown armed men got into the bus and threatened the driver and the commuters with firearms. They then took the driver’s bag, cellphone, staff card and cash, and fired two shots. “They proceeded to rob commuters of their valuables including cash and cellphones, and drove the bus for a short distance. They then parked it and ran away with the keys. “The suspects are unknown and no one was injured during the robbery. A case of robbery with a firearm is being investigated by the police,” said Mohlala. Mpumalanga police commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela said they were looking for the suspects. Anyone with information about the whereabouts of the suspects should call Captain Vusimuzi Mahlangu on 072 407 7012, or call CrimeStop on 08600 10111. Alternatively, members of the public can send information via MYSAPSAPP and all information will be treated as confidential. Callers may opt to remain anonymous.